        "unit": "W",
        "description": "Typical range for Nd:YAG laser cleaning of reflective metals like rare earths; starting at 50W to avoid thermal damage given Praseodymium's low melting point (931°C) and moderate thermal conductivity (~17 W/m·K). Conservative max to prevent substrate melting. Based on manufacturer specs from IPG Photonics for metal cleaning systems; no Praseodymium-specific studies found, generalized from aluminum cleaning (Optics & Laser Technology, 2018)."
